b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe30032.htm)  [Next](sbe30034.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543983862/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 2 (SBE30)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1892], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 101\n\n### PRAP\xc3\x82 _TH_ AKA IV, K\xc3\x82 _N_ _D_ IK\xc3\x82 1.\n\n1. 1 He throws the two spits into the fire;\n\n2\\. That which consists of one (simple) branch, towards the east, the other\none towards the west.\n\n3. 3 They cut off the Avadana portions from all its limbs,\n\n4\\. With the exception of the left thigh and the lungs.\n\n5\\. The left thigh he should keep for the Anvash _t_ akya ceremony.\n\n6. 6 On the same fire he cooks one mess of rice-grains and one of meat, stirring up the one and the other separately, from left to right, with two pot-ladles.\n\n7\\. After he has cooked them, he should pour (\xc3\x82 _g_ ya) on them, should take\nthem from the fire towards the north, and should pour (\xc3\x82 _g_ ya) on them\nagain.\n\n8\\. Having poured the juice (of the Avadanas) into a brazen vessel,\n\n9\\. And having placed the Avadanas on a layer (of grass) on which branches of\nthe Plaksha (tree) have been spread,\n\n10. 10 He cuts off (the prescribed portions) from the\n\np. 102\n\n[paragraph continues] Avadanas in the way prescribed for Sthalipakas, (and\nputs those portions) into (another) brazen vessel;\n\n11\\. And (the portion) for the Svish _t_ ak _ri_ t oblation separately.\n\n12\\. Taking of the mess of boiled rice-grains (Sutra 6) a portion of the size\nof a Bilva fruit, he should mix that, together with the Avadanas (Sutra 10),\nwith the juice (Sutra 8).\n\n13\\. Taking a fourfold portion of \xc3\x82 _g_ ya he should sacrifice it with the\nfirst of the eight _Ri_ _k_ as, 'Entering into fire, the fire' (MB. II, 2,\n9-16).\n\n14\\. Of the mixture (Sutra 12) he cuts off the third part and sacrifices it\nwith the second and third (verse).\n\n15\\. He places the word Svaha after the second (of those verses, i.e. after\nthe third verse of the whole Mantra).\n\n16\\. In the same way he sacrifices the other two-thirds (of that mixture, the\none) with the fourth and fifth (verse), and (the other) with the sixth and\nseventh (verse).\n\n17\\. Having cut off the rest, he should sacrifice the oblation to (Agni) Svish\n_t_ ak _ri_ t with the eighth (verse).\n\n18\\. Even if he be very deficient in wealth, he should celebrate (the Ash _t_\naka) with (the sacrifice of) an animal.\n\n19\\. Or he should sacrifice a Sthalipaka.\n\n20. 20 Or he should offer food to a cow.\n\np. 103\n\n21. 21 Or he should burn down brushwood in the forest and should say, 'This is my Ash _t_ aka.'\n\n22\\. But let him not neglect to do (one of these things). But let him not\nneglect to do (one of these things).\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[101:1](sbe30033.htm#fr_350) 1, 1. Comp. III, 10, 31.\n\n[101:3](sbe30033.htm#fr_351) Comp. \xc3\x82 _s_ valayana-G _ri_ hya I, 11, 12;\nKhadira-G _ri_ hya III, 4, 14 seq.\n\n[101:6](sbe30033.htm#fr_352) 'He cooks a mess of meat'\xc2\x97i.e. he cooks the\nAvadanas. Comp. Khadira-G _ri_ hya, l.l. 17; \xc3\x82 _s_ v.-G _ri_ hya I, 11, 12.\n\n[101:10](sbe30033.htm#fr_353) See I, 8, 5 seq.\n\n[102:20](sbe30033.htm#fr_354) 20 seq. Regarding these Sutras, which occur\nnearly identically in _S_ a\xe1\xb9\x85khayana III, 14, 4 seq., \xc3\x82 _s_ valayana II, 4,\n8-11, comp. the note, vol. xxix, p. 105.\n\n[103:21](sbe30033.htm#fr_355) I believe that we ought to correct upadhaya into\nupadahya. _S_ a\xe1\xb9\x85khayana III, 14, 5: api vara _n_ ye kaksham apadahet. \xc3\x82 _s_\nvalayana II, 4, 9: agnina va kaksham uposhet.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: IV, 2](sbe30034.htm)\n\n"